solution.p:
The third quadrant angle with reference angle \dfrac{\pi}{4} is
\pi + \dfrac{\pi}{4} = \dfrac{5\pi}{4}
 so the second solution is t_2 = \dfrac{5\pi}{4}.

sidebyside.p:
Thus, after \alert{2} minutes your height is
  \begin{align*}
  f(\alert{2}) \amp = 100 - 100\cos (\dfrac{\pi}{2})\\
        \amp = 100 - 100(0) = 100\\
        \end{align*}
  and after \alert{4} minutes your height is
  \begin{align*}
  f(\alert{4}) \amp = 100 - 100\cos (\pi)\\
        \amp = 100 - 100(-1) = 200\\
        \end{align*}
